			"description": "The massless two-loop two-point master topology with five propagators raised to arbitrary (non-integer) powers $\\nu_j = n_j + a_j\\varepsilon$, in generic even dimension $D = 2m - 2\\varepsilon$. The paper derives the integral as a convolution product of two primitive one-loop integrals and, via inverse Mellin transformations followed by closing Mellin-Barnes contours and summing residues, obtains a nested-sum representation that can be expanded to arbitrary order in epsilon. A central theorem (the 'Bierenbaum-Weinzierl theorem') proves that only rational numbers and multiple zeta values appear in the Laurent expansion. Explicit Laurent expansions through $\\mathcal{O}(\\varepsilon^7)$ (transcendental weight 10) are quoted for several parameter choices in Section 5 and were implemented in C++ using nestedsums and GiNaC.",
