			"description": "Two-loop massless kite two-point scalar integral with two composite vertices carrying Bjorken fractions $x$ and $y$ (Dirac deltas on two internal lines). Propagators are $D_1=(k_1-p)^2$, $D_2=(k_2-p)^2$, $D_3=k_1^2$, $D_4=k_2^2$, $D_5=(k_1-k_2)^2$ with arbitrary indices $n_1,...,n_5$ and arbitrary space-time dimension $D$. The integral $I(p;\\{n_i\\};x,y;D)$ is evaluated exactly (all orders in $D$) in the alpha representation and expressed in closed form through the Kampe de Feriet function of two variables; in several special cases it reduces to $3F2$ functions. Twofold Mellin moments are obtained in terms of generalized Lauricella $F^{(3)}$ series and KdF functions. The special case $n_1=n_2=n_3=n_4=1$, $n_5=n$ is treated in Section 5. Called the 'kite' diagram in the paper; see figures 1 and 2 and Eqs. (2.4)-(2.5).",
